<TITLE> Blair hails Fakhruddin on reform efforts </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, June 26 (bdnews24.com)  UK prime minister Tony Blair Monday felicitated chief adviser Fakhruddin Ahmed on his caretaker government's efforts to effect social and economic reforms, the foreign ministry said in a statement Tuesday. Responding to the CA's letter to all the leaders of the G-8 countries prior to their June summit, Blair wrote: "The UK government continues to support these (social and economic) efforts." Blair referred to a recently pledged UK government support of 200,000 to the WTO to establish capacity building in the Least Developed Countries (LDCs) including implementation of the Doha text on Trade Facilitation. Bangladesh has already requested support from the programme, the statement said. Blair said, "I remain open to exploring alternative avenues by which the needs of LDCs may be met through special and differential treatment to ensure a genuinely ambitious, pro- development outcome to the Doha negotiating round." Highlighting trade issues faced by the LDCs, the CA had written the letter on June 22. bd
